3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the time complexity of graph isomorphism, which is a topic within computational complexity. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper uses group theoretic frameworks to solve the multiple-coset isomorphism problem, which has applications in game theory. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for graph isomorphism, which is a core topic in data structures and algorithms.
